242	/**
243	 * PATCH /api/users/[id]
244	 *
245	 * Applies a partial update to a user record; used for targeted field changes (e.g.
246	 * toggling `isEnabled`, updating a single profile field) without sending the full
247	 * document. Identical permission enforcement to PUT — `_id` is stripped from the body
248	 * and the path param is used as the authoritative identifier.
249	 *
250	 * URL params:
251	 * @param id {string} Required (path). The string `_id` of the user to update.
252	 *
253	 * Body fields (all optional; only provided fields are applied):
254	 * @param _id              {string}   Ignored. Stripped before update; the path `id` is used instead.
255	 * @param roles            {string[]} New role list. Triggers `sessionVersion` increment to force re-login.
256	 * @param assignedLocations  {string[]} Location IDs the user is permitted to access.
257	 *                                    Restricted to admin/owner/developer; silently stripped for others.
258	 * @param assignedLicencees  {string[]} Licencee IDs that scope the user's data visibility.
259	 *                                    Restricted to admin/owner/developer; silently stripped for others.
